                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">crude.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>early 20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits and headings of the texts;
                           number of the chapters and the word mǝʿrāf; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; Ethiopic numerals; elements of numbers of the quires; numbers of
                           the “tituli”; on the incipit page of each Gospel, a few lines are
                           rubricated (in groups of two lines, alternating with black lines);
                           Letters ወ and ደ in the word ወልደ used in the genealogy of Christ (fols.
                           94v-95r).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
